FL,399,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39802
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F398A1773191773
OL,3,CD-Day veteran to receive MBE at
OL,4,CWindsor Castle
OL,6,FThe former RAF sergeant, from Crewe,
OL,7,Fwho enlisted on his 18th birthday, was
OL,8,Fjust 20 when landed in Normandy on 6
OL,9,FJune 1944 - making him the youngest
OL,10,Fsergeant from the Royal Air Force to
OL,11,Fserve during the operation.
OL,13,FAs a codebreaker, Bernard held a
OL,14,Funique seat at the table of history.
OL,15,FTwo days before VE Day, he received a
OL,16,Ftop-secret telegram that would change
OL,17,Fthe world.
OL,19,FThe message read: "German war now
OL,20,Fover, surrender effective sometime
OL,21,Ftomorrow."
OL,26,@{D@SOU}D@JO]
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/5
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,399,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39803
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F398A1773191773
OL,3,CD-Day veteran to receive MBE at
OL,4,CWindsor Castle
OL,6,FDespite the monumental nature of the
OL,7,Fnews, he was sworn to secrecy and
OL,8,Funable to celebrate until the official
OL,9,Fannouncement was made to the public.
OL,11,FBernard's diaries offer a harrowing
OL,12,Fglimpse into the reality of the 1944
OL,13,Flandings.
OL,15,FReflecting on his arrival in France,
OL,16,Fhe wrote: "I shall never forget seeing
OL,17,Fthe beach littered with many dead
OL,18,Fbodies, some of whom had been shot or
OL,19,Fdrowned and others carried in by the
OL,20,Fincoming tide."
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/5
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
